'''Nuno Alexandre Tavares Mendes''' ({{IPA|pt|ˈnunu ˈmẽdɨʃ}}; born 19 June 2002) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]]. He is widely regarded as one of the best left-backs in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.givemesport.com/best-defenders-world-football-ranked/|title=25 best defenders in world football right now (ranked)|publisher=Give Me Sport|first1=Callum|last1=Altimas|first2=Calum|last2=Ritchie|date=9 October 2023|access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref><ref name=ESPN>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45164388/2025-fc-100-alexander-arnold-best-fullbacks-mens-soccer|title=2025 FC 100: Alexander-Arnold among best fullbacks in men's soccer|publisher=[[ESPN]]|date=4 June 2025|access-date=9 June 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/ranked-best-left-backs-in-the-world|title=Ranked! The 10 best left-backs in the world|publisher=[[FourFourTwo]]|first=Mark|last=White|date=16 June 2025|access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-left-backs-in-world-soccer-ranked|title=The 25 Best Left Backs in World Soccer — Ranked|publisher=[[Sports Illustrated]]|date=14 July 2025|access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref>

He came through [[Sporting CP]]'s youth academy, making his first-team debut in 2020 and winning a [[Double (association football)|double]] of [[Primeira Liga]] and [[Taça da Liga]] the [[2020–21 Sporting CP season|following season]] while being named in the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Primeira Liga Team of the Year]]. In August 2021, he moved to Paris Saint-Germain on loan, joining the club permanently for €38 million in June 2022. In [[2024–25 Paris Saint-Germain FC season|2024–25]], he was a prominent player as they attained a [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]]; he won several honours during his spell at the latter club, including five [[Ligue 1]] titles and back-to-back [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] titles in [[2025 UEFA Champions League final|2025]] and [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|2026]].

Mendes represented Portugal at various [[Portugal national youth football team|youth levels]]. He made his full debut in 2021, and was chosen in the squads for two [[FIFA World Cup|World Cups]] and as many [[UEFA European Championship|European Championships]]. He won the [[UEFA Nations League]] in [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|2025]], being named the best player of [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|the finals]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Sintra]], [[Lisbon District]] of [[Cape Verdeans in Portugal|Cape Verdean descent]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/sporting/detalhe/nuno-mendes-o-meu-pai-estaria-orgulhoso-de-mim|title=Nuno Mendes: «O meu pai estaria orgulhoso de mim»|trans-title=Nuno Mendes: "My father would be proud of me"|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|first=Ricardo|last=Granada|language=pt|date=31 July 2020|access-date=9 June 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rfi.fr/pt/desporto/20250609-portugal-%C3%A9-campe%C3%A3o-da-liga-das-na%C3%A7%C3%B5es-europeias-de-futebol|title=Portugal é campeão da Liga das nações europeias de futebol|trans-title=Portugal are champions of the League of European nations in football|publisher=[[Radio France Internationale]]|language=pt|date=9 June 2025|access-date=9 June 2025}}</ref> Mendes started playing football aged 9,<ref name=Skills>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/nuno-mendes-wonderkid-left-back-ronaldinho-skills-man-utd/1t3oajpz9nogv1bzx6to8ng2t6|title=Nuno Mendes: The wonderkid left-back with Ronaldinho's skills on Man Utd's radar|publisher=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|first=Tom|last=Maston|date=20 October 2020|access-date=1 November 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211101004546/https://www.goal.com/en/news/nuno-mendes-wonderkid-left-back-ronaldinho-skills-man-utd/1t3oajpz9nogv1bzx6to8ng2t6|archive-date=1 November 2021}}</ref> and his idols growing up were [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], [[Lionel Messi]], [[David Alaba]] and [[Marcelo (footballer, born 1988)|Marcelo]], the two last players being the ones he tried to emulate.<ref name=Skills/> He would be spotted by his school teacher Bruno Botelho, who invited him to play for local club Despertar on the outskirts of [[Lisbon]].<ref name=Skills/> He quickly stood out, subsequently catching the eye of [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], [[FC Porto|Porto]] and [[Sporting CP]] and joining the [[Sporting CP (youth)|latter's youth system]] at the age of 10.<ref name=Skills/><ref name=AD>{{cite web|url=https://oambidestro.pt/2020/05/19/nuno-mendes-o-futuro-dono-da-lateral-esquerda-dos-leoes/|title=Nuno Mendes, o futuro dono da lateral esquerda dos leões|trans-title=Nuno Mendes, the future owner of the Lions' left-back berth|publisher=O Ambidestro|first=Alexandre|last=Ribeiro|language=pt|date=19 May 2020|access-date=12 June 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027041551/https://oambidestro.pt/2020/05/19/nuno-mendes-o-futuro-dono-da-lateral-esquerda-dos-leoes/|archive-date=27 October 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/nuno-mendes-celebra-18-anos-toda-a-historia-da-mais-recente-promessa-do-sporting|title=Acordar para o sonho: a história do início de Nuno Mendes no futebol|trans-title=Waking up to the dream: the story of Nuno Mendes' football beginnings|newspaper=Record|first=David|last=Novo|language=pt|date=19 June 2020|access-date=21 October 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021130742/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-bwin/sporting/detalhe/nuno-mendes-celebra-18-anos-toda-a-historia-da-mais-recente-promessa-do-sporting|archive-date=21 October 2021}}</ref>

During his [[Scout (sport)|scouting]] process, as he returned home from school, Mendes realised he was being followed by a man. For fear of being robbed, he ran home, located in a very poor neighbourhood; the "stalker" was actually a Sporting scout, who later convinced him to sign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/br/not%C3%ADcias/Quando-o-sporting-bateu-a-porta-de-nuno-mendes-nao-era/1727kdavveroo1l4rrlcdtqqgr|title=Quando o Sporting bateu à porta de Nuno Mendes: não era assalto, era oportunidade de vida|trans-title=When Sporting knocked on Nuno Mendes's door: it wasn't a robbery, it was a chance for life|publisher=Goal|first=Bruno|last=Andrade|language=pt|date=8 January 2021|access-date=29 September 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210929114835/https://www.goal.com/br/not%C3%ADcias/Quando-o-sporting-bateu-a-porta-de-nuno-mendes-nao-era/1727kdavveroo1l4rrlcdtqqgr|archive-date=29 September 2021}}</ref> He spent the next four years making a two-hour round trip in order to train every night with his teacher, before moving to Sporting's academy at the age of 14.<ref name=Skills/>

Mendes initially played as an [[attacking midfielder]] before being converted to a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]], a position he struggled with in the beginning.<ref name=Skills/>

===Sporting CP===
[[File:Nuno Mendes.jpg|thumb|Mendes with [[Sporting CP]] in 2021]]
Following the outbreak of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]] in February, which brought a premature end to the youth football season, Mendes was one of a small group of youth players to be called up to the first team by manager [[Ruben Amorim]], despite having only played once since November due to an injury.<ref name=Skills/> He made his professional debut in a 1–0 [[Primeira Liga]] home win against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]] on 12 June 2020, as a 72nd-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Marcos Acuña]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/sporting-bate-pacos-de-ferreira-com-grande-golo-de-jovane|title=Sporting bate Paços de Ferreira com grande golo de Jovane|trans-title=Sporting beat Paços de Ferreira with great Jovane goal|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=12 June 2020|access-date=12 November 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210310053319/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/sporting-bate-pacos-de-ferreira-com-grande-golo-de-jovane|archive-date=10 March 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/nuno-mendes-estreou-se-aos-17-anos-pela-equipa-principal-do-sporting|title=Nuno Mendes estreou-se aos 17 anos pela equipa principal do Sporting|trans-title=Nuno Mendes made debut for Sporting's first team aged 17|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=12 June 2020|access-date=26 June 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116041702/https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/sporting/detalhe/nuno-mendes-estreou-se-aos-17-anos-pela-equipa-principal-do-sporting|archive-date=16 January 2021}}</ref><ref name=Skills/>

After the latter left for [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the 2020 off-season, Mendes became first choice at only 18, becoming the youngest player to make the club's starting XI since Ronaldo in September 2002;<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/dois-tubaroes-perguntaram-por-nuno-mendes-eis-a-resposta-do-sporting-12698124.html|title=Dois "tubarões" perguntaram por Nuno Mendes: eis a resposta do Sporting|trans-title=Two "sharks" asked about Nuno Mendes: here's what Sporting replied|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|first1=Duarte|last1=Tornesi|first2=Rui Miguel|last2=Gomes|language=pt|date=7 September 2020|access-date=12 November 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127014257/https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/sporting/noticias/dois-tubaroes-perguntaram-por-nuno-mendes-eis-a-resposta-do-sporting-12698124.html|archive-date=27 January 2021}}</ref><ref name=Skills/> he went onto start six of his side's seven remaining league matches.<ref name=Skills/> He scored his first competitive goal for them on 4 October of the same year, in the 2–0 away victory over [[Portimonense S.C.|Portimonense]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2020/10/04/nuno-mendes-nao-desiste-por-ele-e-pelo-clube-a-cronica-do-portimonense-sporting/|title=Nuno Mendes não desiste. Por ele e pelo clube (a crónica do Portimonense-Sporting)|trans-title=Nuno Mendes does not quit. For him and for club (Portimonense-Sporting match report)|newspaper=[[Observador]]|first=Bruno|last=Roseiro|language=pt|date=4 October 2020|access-date=11 November 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105043754/https://observador.pt/2020/10/04/nuno-mendes-nao-desiste-por-ele-e-pelo-clube-a-cronica-do-portimonense-sporting/|archive-date=5 November 2020}}</ref>

Mendes agreed to a contract extension on 19 December 2020, increasing his [[buyout clause]] from €45 million to €70 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/inter-linked-nuno-mendes-extends-contract-with-sporting-lisbon-portuguese-media-report-32001816|title=Inter linked Nuno Mendes extends contract with Sporting Lisbon, Portuguese media report|publisher=[[OneFootball]]|date=19 December 2020|access-date=22 December 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211019033946/https://onefootball.com/en/news/inter-linked-nuno-mendes-extends-contract-with-sporting-lisbon-portuguese-media-report-32001816|archive-date=19 October 2021}}</ref> He played 29 games for the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga|eventual champions]], while also being named in the [[2020–21 Primeira Liga#Annual awards|Team of the Year]].<ref name=PL>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/2080-10-reasons-why-sporting-are-champions-of-portugal|title=10 reasons why Sporting are Champions of Portugal|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Tom|last=Kundert|date=11 May 2021|access-date=25 May 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512123545/https://portugoal.net/club-news/2080-10-reasons-why-sporting-are-champions-of-portugal|archive-date=12 May 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/joao-palhinha-do-sporting-no-melhor-onze-da-ultima-edicao-da-i-liga-13814732.html|title=João Palhinha, do Sporting, no melhor onze da última edição da I Liga|trans-title=João Palhinha, of Sporting, in the All-Star XI of I League's last edition|publisher=[[TSF (radio station)|TSF]]|language=pt|date=8 June 2021|access-date=21 October 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021091820/https://www.tsf.pt/desporto/joao-palhinha-do-sporting-no-melhor-onze-da-ultima-edicao-da-i-liga-13814732.html|archive-date=21 October 2021}}</ref>

On 31 July 2021, Mendes provided an [[Assist (association football)|assist]] for [[Jovane Cabral]] in the 2–1 defeat of [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] and [[2021 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|conquest]] of the [[Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-portugues/noticia/sporting-vence-braga-de-virada-e-conquista-supertaca-de-portugal.ghtml|title=Sporting vence Braga de virada e conquista Supertaça de Portugal|trans-title=Sporting beat Braga with comeback and win Portuguese Supercup|publisher=[[TV Globo|Globo Esporte]]|language=pt|date=31 July 2021|access-date=21 October 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021130748/https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-portugues/noticia/sporting-vence-braga-de-virada-e-conquista-supertaca-de-portugal.ghtml|archive-date=21 October 2021}}</ref>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
====2021–23: First league titles and Ligue Young Player of the Year====
On 31 August 2021, Mendes joined [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] on a [[2021–22 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|season]]-long loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/nuno-mendes-joins-paris-saint-germain-until-2022-mercato|title=Nuno Mendes joins Paris Saint-Germain|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=31 August 2021|access-date=31 August 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831223948/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/nuno-mendes-joins-paris-saint-germain-until-2022-mercato|archive-date=31 August 2021}}</ref> He made his [[Ligue 1]] debut for the club on 11 September, coming on as a 85th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 4–0 defeat of [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/debuts-for-gianluigi-donnarumma-nuno-mendes-and-nathan-bitumazala-paris-saint-germain-clermont-foot-63-ligue-1-2021-2022|title=Debuts for Donnarumma, Nuno Mendes and Bitumazala|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=11 September 2021|access-date=15 September 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210916080139/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/debuts-for-gianluigi-donnarumma-nuno-mendes-and-nathan-bitumazala-paris-saint-germain-clermont-foot-63-ligue-1-2021-2022|archive-date=16 September 2021}}</ref> He appeared in his first game in the [[UEFA Champions League]] four days later, replacing [[Abdou Diallo]] 75 minutes into a 1–1 draw away to [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] in the [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|group stage]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58577370|title=Club Bruges 1–1 Paris Saint Germain|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|first=Alex|last=Bysouth|date=15 September 2021|access-date=20 September 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210919124850/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58577370|archive-date=19 September 2021}}</ref> he had an instant impact on the [[Pitch (sports field)|pitch]], notably making a "brilliant" run to set up a shooting opportunity for [[Lionel Messi]] at the 77th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.highpresssoccer.com/psg-player-ratings-vs-club-brugge-messi/|title=PSG player ratings vs Club Brugge: Messi's march to 5th UCL trophy begins|publisher=High Press Soccer|first=Uttiyo|last=Sarkar|date=15 September 2021|access-date=15 September 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120084713/https://www.highpresssoccer.com/psg-player-ratings-vs-club-brugge-messi/|archive-date=20 January 2022}}</ref> He made his first start later that month, in a 2–1 win over [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/paris-pip-lyon-at-the-post-match-report-summary-paris-saint-germain-olympique-lyonnais-psg-ligue-1|title=Paris pip Lyon at the post!|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=19 September 2021|access-date=19 September 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210920211840/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/paris-pip-lyon-at-the-post-match-report-summary-paris-saint-germain-olympique-lyonnais-psg-ligue-1|archive-date=20 September 2021}}</ref> He helped PSG to win their record-tying 10th national championship by making 27 appearances (18 starts),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://global.espn.com/football/paris-saint-germain--frapsg/story/4646307/lionel-messi-scores-as-paris-saint-germain-win-ligue-1-to-equal-marseillesaint-etienne-title-record|title=Messi scores as PSG win title, equal Ligue 1 mark|publisher=ESPN|date=23 April 2022|access-date=31 May 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220424053625/https://global.espn.com/football/paris-saint-germain--frapsg/story/4646307/lionel-messi-scores-as-paris-saint-germain-win-ligue-1-to-equal-marseillesaint-etienne-title-record|archive-date=24 April 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://psgtalk.com/2022/05/report-nuno-mendes-future-at-psg-gets-a-pivotal-update/|title=Report: Nuno Mendes' future at PSG gets a pivotal update|publisher=PSG Talk|first=Steve|last=Zavala|date=27 May 2022|access-date=5 June 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220605210919/https://psgtalk.com/2022/05/report-nuno-mendes-future-at-psg-gets-a-pivotal-update/|archive-date=5 June 2022}}</ref> and later was nominated to the [[Ligue 1 Young Player of the Year|Young Player of the Year]] award and named to the [[Trophées UNFP du football#Team of the Year|Team of the Year]] alongside two of his teammates.<ref name=GFFN>{{cite web|url=https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2022/kylian-mbappe-named-ligue-1-player-of-the-year/|title=Kylian Mbappé named Ligue 1 player of the year|publisher=Get French Football News|date=15 May 2022|access-date=15 May 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230610214549/https://www.getfootballnewsfrance.com/2022/kylian-mbappe-named-ligue-1-player-of-the-year/|archive-date=10 June 2023}}</ref><ref name=EQUIPE1>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-equipe-type-de-la-saison-de-ligue-1-aux-trophees-unfp-avec-un-trio-d-attaque-terrier-ben-yedder-mbappe/1333260|title=L'équipe type de la saison de Ligue 1 aux trophées UNFP avec un trio d'attaque Terrier-Ben Yedder-Mbappé|trans-title=All-star team of Ligue 1 at UNFP trophies with attacking trio Terrier-Ben Yedder-Mbappé|newspaper=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr|date=15 May 2022|access-date=31 May 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220601035838/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-equipe-type-de-la-saison-de-ligue-1-aux-trophees-unfp-avec-un-trio-d-attaque-terrier-ben-yedder-mbappe/1333260|archive-date=1 June 2022}}</ref>

On 31 May 2022, Mendes' buyout clause of €38 million was triggered and he signed a permanent four-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/liga-francesa/2022/05/31/6295db3922601d7f028b45cb.html|title=El PSG ficha de forma permanente a Nuno Mendes por 40 millones de euros|trans-title=PSG sign Nuno Mendes permanently for 40 million euros|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=31 May 2022|access-date=31 May 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531092756/https://www.marca.com/futbol/liga-francesa/2022/05/31/6295db3922601d7f028b45cb.html|archive-date=31 May 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/fabrizioromano/status/1531555528144453632|title=Official and confirmed. Paris Saint-Germain announce Nuno Mendes deal completed with Sporting by triggering the buy option clause.|publisher=[[Twitter]]|first=Fabrizio|last=Romano|date=31 May 2022|access-date=31 May 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531083830/https://twitter.com/FabrizioRomano/status/1531555528144453632|archive-date=31 May 2022}}</ref> He scored his first official goal on 3 September, closing a 3–0 away victory against [[FC Nantes|Nantes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/news-starting-understand-messi-s-run-beautiful-see-psg-fans-hail-performance-terrific-player-3-0-win-nantes|title="Starting to understand Messi's run", "Beautiful to see" – PSG fans hail performance from 'terrific' player after 3–0 win against Nantes|publisher=Sportskeeda|first=Apratim|last=Banerjee|date=4 September 2022|access-date=4 September 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220903235114/https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/news-starting-understand-messi-s-run-beautiful-see-psg-fans-hail-performance-terrific-player-3-0-win-nantes|archive-date=3 September 2022}}</ref> His first in the Champions League came on 2 November, the winner in a 2–1 victory away to [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|last group fixture]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lepoint.fr/sport/football/ligue-des-champions-juventus-psg-a-suivre-en-direct-des-21-heures-02-11-2022-2496253_1858.php#11|title=Ligue des champions: le PSG bat la Juve mais termine 2e de son groupe|trans-title=Champions League: PSG beat Juve but finish 2nd in their group|publisher=[[Le Point]]|first=Guillaume|last=Paret|language=fr|date=2 November 2022|access-date=2 November 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221102145720/https://www.lepoint.fr/sport/football/ligue-des-champions-juventus-psg-a-suivre-en-direct-des-21-heures-02-11-2022-2496253_1858.php#11|archive-date=2 November 2022}}</ref> During [[2022–23 Ligue 1|the season]], he was a key contributor to his team's record 11th title,<ref name=DN>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/psg-novamente-campeao-em-franca-com-empate-em-estrasburgo-16431023.html|title=PSG novamente campeão em França com empate em Estrasburgo|trans-title=PSG champions in France again with draw in Strasbourg|newspaper=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt|date=27 May 2023|access-date=28 May 2023|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230527234457/https://www.dn.pt/desporto/psg-novamente-campeao-em-franca-com-empate-em-estrasburgo-16431023.html|archive-date=27 May 2023}}</ref> winning the Young Player of the Year and being included in the Team of the Year in the process.<ref name=MSN>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/other/nuno-mendes-named-young-player-of-the-year-for-2022-23-season/ar-AA1bPH2P|title=Nuno Mendes named Young Player of the Year for 2022/23 season|publisher=[[MSN]]|first=Antonio|last=Losada|date=28 May 2023|access-date=29 May 2023|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230529132009/http://www.msn.com/en-us/sports/other/nuno-mendes-named-young-player-of-the-year-for-2022-23-season/ar-AA1bPH2P|archive-date=29 May 2023}}</ref><ref name=EQUIPE2>{{cite news|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Messi-rongier-danso-l-equipe-type-de-la-saison-de-ligue-1/1399239|title=Messi, Rongier, Danso... L'équipe type de la saison de Ligue 1|trans-title=Messi, Rongier, Danso... Ligue 1's All-Star Team of the Season|newspaper=L'Équipe|language=fr|date=28 May 2023|access-date=29 May 2023|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230603053146/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Messi-rongier-danso-l-equipe-type-de-la-saison-de-ligue-1/1399239|archive-date=3 June 2023}}</ref>

====2023–present: Injury issues and continental treble====
[[File:FC Salzburg gegen Paris Saint-Germain UEFA Champions League 85 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Mendes with [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] in 2024]]
Mendes had suffered from a hamstring injury since May 2023, and was successfully operated in October by surgeon Lasse Lempainen in [[Turku]], Finland.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ts.fi/urheilu/6119552|title=Portugalin maajoukkuefutaaja Nuno Mendes operoitiin Turussa – PSG:n puolustajalla edessään kuukausien toipumisjakso|trans-title=Portugal national team player Nuno Mendes underwent surgery in Turku – PSG defender faces long recovery|newspaper=[[Turun Sanomat]]|first=Joonas|last=Jussila|language=fi|date=2 October 2023|access-date=7 January 2024|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240107115617/https://www.ts.fi/urheilu/6119552|archive-date=7 January 2024}}</ref> He only made his return on 25 February 2024, playing 20 minutes of the 1–1 league home draw against [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] in place of [[Lucas Hernandez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/psg-rennes-nuno-mendes-a-fait-son-grand-retour-sur-le-terrain-10-mois-apres-sa-blessure_AV-202402250390.html|title=PSG-Rennes: Nuno Mendes a fait son grand retour sur le terrain 10 mois après sa blessure|trans-title=PSG-Rennes: Nuno Mendes has made his big return to the pitches 10 months after his injury|publisher=[[RMC (France)|RMC]]|language=fr|date=25 February 2024|access-date=26 February 2024|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240225231713/https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/psg-rennes-nuno-mendes-a-fait-son-grand-retour-sur-le-terrain-10-mois-apres-sa-blessure_AV-202402250390.html|archive-date=25 February 2024}}</ref> He eventually helped his team to reach the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League semi-finals]], where they were knocked out by [[Borussia Dortmund]] 2–0 on aggregate;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/psg-dortmund-live-updates-champions-league-score-result/noPrBVsoDvsb/|title=How Borussia Dortmund beat PSG to advance to Champions League final|publisher=[[The Athletic]]|first=Michael|last=Dominski|date=7 May 2024|access-date=16 July 2024}}</ref> they also won the [[Treble (association football)|domestic treble]] with record-extending successes in [[2023–24 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]], the [[Coupe de France]] and the [[Trophée des Champions]], with the player only not taking part in the latter due to his injury.<ref name=LIGUE24>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/paris-saint-germain-win-their-12th-ligue-1-title-psg-ligue-1-club-2023-2024|title=Paris Saint-Germain win their 12th Ligue 1 title!|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=28 April 2024|access-date=28 April 2024|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240428192841/https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/paris-saint-germain-win-their-12th-ligue-1-title-psg-ligue-1-club-2023-2024|archive-date=28 April 2024}}</ref><ref name=COUPE24>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/psg-beat-lyon-2-1-french-cup-final-clinch-domestic-treble-2024-05-25/|title=PSG beat Lyon 2–1 to win French Cup final in Mbappe's farewell appearance|publisher=[[Reuters]]|date=25 May 2024|access-date=25 May 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/coupe-de-france/psg-enrique-a-la-recherche-de-joueurs-qui-veulent-venir-marquer-l-histoire-du-club-20240526|title="La Ligue des champions, on la gagnera": Luis Enrique confiant et (très) ambitieux pour l'après-Mbappé au PSG|trans-title="The Champions League, we will win it": Luis Enrique confident and (very) ambitious for PSG's post-Mbappé|newspaper=[[Le Figaro]]|first=Christophe|last=Remise|language=fr|date=25 May 2024|access-date=16 July 2024|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240525225608/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/coupe-de-france/psg-enrique-a-la-recherche-de-joueurs-qui-veulent-venir-marquer-l-histoire-du-club-20240526|archive-date=25 May 2024}}</ref>

On 9 February 2025, Mendes agreed to an extension until 2029.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/nuno-mendes-happy-to-be-part-of-psgs-history-psg-equipe-premiere-interview-2024-2025|title=Nuno Mendes: "Happy to be part of PSG's history"|publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|date=9 February 2025|access-date=9 February 2025}}</ref> Ten days later, in the second leg of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League knockout phase play-offs]], he scored PSG's fifth goal in the 7–0 win over fellow French [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]], helping his side to a 10–0 aggregate victory;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c98y71v52ngt|title=PSG 7–0 Brest: French champions stroll into last 16 with 10–0 aggregate win|publisher=BBC Sport|date=19 February 2025|access-date=24 February 2025}}</ref> he also found the net in both legs of the quarter-finals against [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] (3–1 home victory, 3–2 away loss),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11945/13344321/psg-3-1-aston-villa-desire-doue-khvicha-kvaratskhelia-nuno-mendes-earn-champions-league-quarter-final-first-leg-victory|title=PSG 3–1 Aston Villa: Desire Doue, Khvicha Kvaratskhelia, Nuno Mendes earn Champions League quarter-final first leg victory|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|date=10 April 2025|access-date=10 April 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/ckgr4n77yy3t|title=Aston Villa 3–2 PSG|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Phil|last=McNulty|date=15 April 2025|access-date=15 April 2025}}</ref> achieving the continental treble by winning the [[2024–25 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]], the [[2024–25 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]] and a first-ever Champions League after a 5–0 defeat of [[Inter Milan]] in [[2025 UEFA Champions League final|the final]], being named in the latter competition's Team of the Season;<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles-video/psg-dominate-the-uefa-champions-league-team-of-the-season-with-seven-players-2025-06-01|title=PSG dominate the UEFA Champions League Team of the Season with seven players|publisher=[[beIN Sports]]|date=1 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref> his performances led to him emerging as a contender for the [[2025 Ballon d'Or]], finally ranking 10th.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/ballon-d-or/ballon-d-or/bola-de-ouro-para-nuno-mendes-so-tres-defesas-venceram-galardao|title=Bola de Ouro para Nuno Mendes? Só três defesas venceram galardão|trans-title=Ballon d'Or to Nuno Mendes? Only three defenders won the award|publisher=Mais Futebol|first=David|last=Silva|language=pt|date=9 June 2025|access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/2025/09/22/bola-de-ouro-vitinha-e-nuno-mendes-entram-no-top-10-gyokeres-fica-em-15-o-e-joao-neves-acaba-em-19-o/|title=Bola de Ouro. Dembélé vence Lamine com Vitinha a fechar o pódio, Nuno Mendes no top 10 e João Neves em 3.º no prémio Kopa|trans-title=Ballon d'Or. Dembélé beats Lamine with Vitinha completing podium, Nuno Mendes in the top 10 and João Neves 3rd in the Kopa award|newspaper=Observador|first=Bruno|last=Roseiro|language=pt|date=22 September 2025|access-date=5 October 2025}}</ref>

On 5 October 2025, Mendes scored the first [[Free kick (association football)|free kick]] of his career, opening a 1–1 away draw against [[Lille OSC|Lille]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/portuguese-abroad/5155-nuno-mendes-adds-free-kicks-to-repertoire-with-stunning-strike-for-psg-video|title=Nuno Mendes adds free-kicks to repertoire with stunning strike for PSG [video]|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Sean|last=Gillen|date=6 October 2025|access-date=6 October 2025}}</ref> He [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League|won his second Champions League]] at the end of [[2025–26 Ligue 1|the campaign]]; in [[2026 UEFA Champions League final|the final]] against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]], however, he had his attempt in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] saved by [[David Raya]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4672287/arsenal-suffer-heartbreaking-end-to-epic-season|title=Arsenal suffer heartbreaking end to epic season|publisher=[[Premier League]]|first=Sam|last=Cunningham|date=30 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Mendes earned his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] for [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 level]] shortly after having made his club debut, in a 4–0 win in [[Cyprus national under-21 football team|Cyprus]] for the [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|2021 UEFA European Championship]] [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|qualifiers]] on 4 September 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ominho.pt/rui-jorge-estreia-tres-jogadores-do-sporting-e-um-do-benfica-nos-sub-21/|title=Rui Jorge estreia três jogadores do Sporting e um do Benfica nos sub-21|trans-title=Rui Jorge gives debut to three Sporting players and one from Benfica in under-21s|newspaper=O Minho|language=pt|date=24 August 2020|access-date=12 November 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220318202359/https://ominho.pt/rui-jorge-estreia-tres-jogadores-do-sporting-e-um-do-benfica-nos-sub-21/|archive-date=18 March 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao-nacional/portugal-sub21/sub21-portugal-goleia-em-chipre-e-diogo-leite-bisa|title=Sub21: Portugal goleia em Chipre e Diogo Leite bisa|trans-title=Under21: Portugal rout in Cyprus and Diogo Leite grabs brace|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=pt|date=4 September 2020|access-date=12 November 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201116160224/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao-nacional/portugal-sub21/sub21-portugal-goleia-em-chipre-e-diogo-leite-bisa|archive-date=16 November 2020}}</ref> Previously, he represented the nation's [[Portugal national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[Portugal national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Portugal national under-18 football team|under-18]] and [[Portugal national under-19 football team|under-19s]].<ref name=AD/>

Six months later, Mendes was called up to the senior team by manager [[Fernando Santos (footballer, born 1954)|Fernando Santos]] for [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifying matches]] against [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]], [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] and [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-portugues/noticia/fernando-santos-convoca-portugal-e-exalta-cristiano-ronaldo-tem-o-sonho-de-vencer-a-copa.ghtml|title=Fernando Santos convoca Portugal e exalta Cristiano Ronaldo: "Tem o sonho de vencer a Copa"|trans-title=Fernando Santos calls Portugal and praises Cristiano Ronaldo: "He dreams of winning the Cup"|publisher=Globo Esporte|language=pt|date=16 March 2021|access-date=21 October 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021130740/https://ge.globo.com/futebol/futebol-internacional/futebol-portugues/noticia/fernando-santos-convoca-portugal-e-exalta-cristiano-ronaldo-tem-o-sonho-de-vencer-a-copa.ghtml|archive-date=21 October 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/selecao/2008-sporting-duo-nuno-mendes-and-joao-palhinha-called-into-portugal-squad-as-cedric-earns-recall|title=Sporting duo Nuno Mendes and João Palhinha called into Portugal squad as Cédric earns recall|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Tom|last=Kundert|date=16 March 2021|access-date=24 March 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210318175132/https://portugoal.net/selecao/2008-sporting-duo-nuno-mendes-and-joao-palhinha-called-into-portugal-squad-as-cedric-earns-recall|archive-date=18 March 2021}}</ref> and subsequently removed from the under-21 squad due to appear in the finals.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.publico.pt/2021/03/15/desporto/noticia/convocados-portugal-europeu-sub21-1954490|title=Os convocados de Portugal para o Europeu sub-21|trans-title=Portugal's squad for under-21 Euro|newspaper=[[Público (Portugal)|Público]]|language=pt|date=15 March 2021|access-date=4 October 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211004155044/https://www.publico.pt/2021/03/15/desporto/noticia/convocados-portugal-europeu-sub21-1954490|archive-date=4 October 2021}}</ref> He first appeared with the former on 24 March 2021, playing the entire 1–0 victory against Azerbaijan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/selecao/2025-portugal-beat-azerbaijan-1-0-in-opening-world-cup-qualifier|title=Portugal beat Azerbaijan 1–0 in opening World Cup qualifier|publisher=PortuGOAL|date=24 March 2021|access-date=24 March 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325154453/https://portugoal.net/selecao/2025-portugal-beat-azerbaijan-1-0-in-opening-world-cup-qualifier|archive-date=25 March 2021}}</ref>

Mendes was selected for [[UEFA Euro 2020]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/features/portugal-euro-2020-squad-the-complete-line-up-for-marchs-internationals|title=Portugal Euro 2020 squad update: full team preview|publisher=FourFourTwo|date=13 June 2021|access-date=31 August 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210606213508/https://www.fourfourtwo.com/us/features/portugal-euro-2020-squad-the-complete-line-up-for-marchs-internationals|archive-date=6 June 2021}}</ref> playing no games in a round-of-16 exit.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://observador.pt/especiais/euro-2020-grupo-f-portugal-o-campeao-que-leva-mala-tabaco-e-qualidade-como-nunca-para-so-voltar-daqui-a-um-mes/|title=Euro 2020 (grupo F). Portugal, o campeão que leva mala, tabaco e qualidade como nunca para só voltar daqui a um mês|trans-title=Euro 2020 (group F). Portugal, the champions who take suitcase, cigarettes and talent like never before to return only a month later|newspaper=Observador|first=Mariana|last=Fernandes|language=pt|date=10 June 2021|access-date=1 September 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210901102349/https://observador.pt/especiais/euro-2020-grupo-f-portugal-o-campeao-que-leva-mala-tabaco-e-qualidade-como-nunca-para-so-voltar-daqui-a-um-mes/|archive-date=1 September 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024479--belgium-vs-portugal/postmatch/report/|title=Belgium 1–0 Portugal: Holders dethroned by Thorgan Hazard|publisher=UEFA|date=27 June 2021|access-date=1 September 2021|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627230649/https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024479--belgium-vs-portugal/postmatch/report/|archive-date=27 June 2021}}</ref> Santos later revealed that he had planned to use him alongside [[Raphaël Guerreiro]] during the tournament, but could not do so due to injury problems.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/artigo/fernando-santos-explica-nao-utilizacao-de-nuno-mendes-e-pote-no-euro2020/13881061/|title=Fernando Santos explica não utilização de Nuno Mendes e Pote no Euro'2020|trans-title=Fernando Santos explains why Nuno Mendes and Pote were not used in Euro'2020|newspaper=O Jogo|language=pt|date=27 June 2021|access-date=4 October 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404171139/https://www.ojogo.pt/internacional/euro-2020/noticias/amp/fernando-santos-explica-nao-utilizacao-de-nuno-mendes-e-pote-no-euro2020-13881061.html|archive-date=4 April 2023}}</ref>

In November 2022, Mendes was named in the final squad for the World Cup in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|title=Os 26 convocados de Portugal: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio e Matheus Nunes chamados|trans-title=Portugal select 26: Gonçalo Ramos, António Silva, Otávio and Matheus Nunes called|publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]]|language=pt|date=10 November 2022|access-date=10 November 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221110174203/https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/mundial/artigos/os-26-convocados-de-portugal-para-o-mundial2022|archive-date=10 November 2022}}</ref> After a first-half thigh injury in the second group-stage match against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]], he missed the rest of the competition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/mundial/mundial-2022/portugal/detalhe/nuno-mendes-falha-o-resto-do-mundial?ref=HP_Ultimas|title=Nuno Mendes falha o resto do Mundial|trans-title=Nuno Mendes misses rest of the World Cup|newspaper=Record|first=Bruno|last=Fernandes|language=pt|date=30 November 2022|access-date=30 November 2022|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704163807/https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/mundial/mundial-2022/portugal/detalhe/nuno-mendes-falha-o-resto-do-mundial?ref=HP_Ultimas|archive-date=4 July 2024}}</ref>

During [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|qualifying]] for [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]], Mendes made one appearance against Luxembourg, assisting Cristiano Ronaldo's opening goal of the 6–0 win in the ninth minute;<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/competicoes-de-selecoes/europeu/euro-2024/detalhe/nuno-mendes-conseguimos-executar-bem-o-que-tinhamos-feito-no-treino|title=Nuno Mendes: "Conseguimos executar bem o que tínhamos feito no treino"|trans-title=Nuno Mendes: "We were able to execute what we had done in training well"|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=26 March 2023|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> he missed the remainder of the campaign with a hamstring injury,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://portugoal.net/portuguese-abroad/3435-portugal-defender-nuno-mendes-out-until-2024|title=Portugal defender Nuno Mendes out until 2024|publisher=PortuGOAL|first=Sean|last=Gillen|date=28 September 2023|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> as Portugal won all ten matches in [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group J|Group J]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/euro-qualificacao/artigos/dez-em-dez-portugal-bate-islandia-faz-historia-e-termina-qualificacao-para-o-euro2024-so-com-vitorias|title=Dez em dez! Portugal bate Islândia, faz história e termina qualificação para o Euro2024 só com vitórias|trans-title=Ten in ten! Portugal beat Iceland, make history and finish qualification for Euro2024 only with wins|publisher=SAPO|first=Pedro Miguel|last=Marques|language=pt|date=19 November 2023|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> He was picked for the finals in Germany,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx88ljwp5x8o|title=Ronaldo named in Portugal squad for Euro 2024|publisher=BBC Sport|date=21 May 2024|access-date=2 July 2024|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240624200925/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx88ljwp5x8o|archive-date=24 June 2024}}</ref> starting against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c3ggyn075p8t|title=Portugal 2–1 Czech Republic|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Gary|last=Rose|date=18 June 2024|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> and [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] in the group phase<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c511d502dxvt|title=Turkey 0–3 Portugal|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=22 June 2024|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> and [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]] (3–0 victory in a penalty shootout)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/crgkd32x07zt?page=17|title=Portugal 0–0 Slovenia (Portugal win 3–0 on pens)|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=1 July 2024|access-date=4 July 2024}}</ref> and [[France national football team|France]] in the knockout stage (5–3 loss in another shootout).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cy79llev4znt|title=Portugal 0–0 France (France win 5–3 on pens)|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emma|last=Sanders|date=5 July 2024|access-date=6 July 2024}}</ref>

Mendes was selected for the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fpf.pt/pt/News/Todas-as-notícias/Notícia/news/50645|title=Convocatória para Liga das Nações divulgada|trans-title=Nations League squad announced|publisher=[[Portuguese Football Federation]]|language=pt|date=20 May 2025|access-date=13 June 2025}}</ref> On 4 June, he assisted Ronaldo for the 2–1 winner in the semi-finals against [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj6rw18xk1yt|title=Germany 1–2 Portugal|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Michael|last=Emons|date=4 June 2025|access-date=9 June 2025}}</ref> He scored his first international goal four days later in a 2–2 draw against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|the final]]; he was crucial in defending [[Lamine Yamal]] throughout the match, and also converted his attempt in the 5–3 shootout win, being named [[player of the match]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6408339/2025/06/08/spain-portugal-yamal-mendes-ronaldo/|title=Spain 2 Portugal 2 (3–5 on pens): Mendes vs Yamal, Ronaldo being Ronaldo, and World Cup chances|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|first=Tim|last1=Spiers|first2=Dermot|last2=Corrigan|first3=Stu|last3=James|date=8 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref> and best player of the tournament.<ref name=UNLPF>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefanationsleague/news/029a-1df453c49ada-5d8aff31f9c2-1000/|title=Nuno Mendes named 2025 UEFA Nations League Player of the Finals|publisher=UEFA|date=8 June 2025|access-date=8 June 2025}}</ref>

Mendes was included in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2026/05/19/the-reason-portugal-called-up-4-goalkeepers-for-world-cup-reason-to-fret-for-cristiano-ronaldo-fans.html|title=The reason Portugal called up 4 goalkeepers for World Cup: No reason to fret for Cristiano Ronaldo fans|newspaper=Marca|first=Matias|last=Wodner|date=19 May 2026|access-date=1 June 2026}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Mendes is known for his offensive capabilities, speed and technical qualities, playing mainly as a left-sided attacking full-back or [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wing-back]], which allows him to create danger either from a standing start or whilst on the counter-attack. Apart from his dribbling, he boasts an excellent [[Cross (association football)|crossing]] ability whether tightly marked or open in space, and his physical prowess allows him to beat out opponents to the ball either with his speed or strength. He is also capable of anticipating attacks and cutting in front of a pass and winning the ball back.<ref name=BTL>{{cite web|url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/player-analysis-nuno-mendes/|title=Player analysis: Nuno Mendes|publisher=Breaking The Lines|first=Jaime|last=Silva|date=17 April 2021|access-date=1 November 2021|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211101130512/https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/player-analysis-nuno-mendes/|archive-date=1 November 2021}}</ref><ref name=ETT>{{cite web|url=https://extratimetalk.com/nuno-mendes-best-left-back-in-the-world/|title=Nuno Mendes cements his status as the best left-back in the world|publisher=Extratime Talk|first=Subhadeep|last=Roy|date=11 June 2025|access-date=14 June 2025}}</ref><ref name=BIS>{{cite web|url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-nations-league/articles/martinez-calls-nuno-mendes-best-left-back-hes-ever-seen-in-ballon-dor-backing-2025-06-11|title=Martinez calls Nuno Mendes 'best left-back he's ever seen' in Ballon d'Or backing|publisher=beIN Sports|date=11 June 2025|access-date=14 June 2025}}</ref><ref name=UNLPF/><ref name=ESPN/>

Despite his ability going forward, however, the defensive side of Mendes's game was brought into question by pundits early into his career, with the latter citing the inconsistency on his decision-making in front of goal, positioning and awareness as areas of weakness in need of improvement.<ref name=BTL/> Over the following years, however, under [[Luis Enrique]] at Paris Saint-Germain, he became more tactically disciplined, displaying better judgment on when to push forward and when to hold his line. His one-on-one defending matured, committing fewer rash challenges while displaying greater awareness of space and opponents’ movement. These developments were particularly evident in high-stakes matches, where his defensive performances against players such as [[Mohamed Salah]] and Yamal drew praise from pundits and coaches alike, marked his improvement into a more complete and balanced full-back.<ref name=ETT/><ref name=BIS/><ref name=UNLPF/>

